I n t r o d u c t i o n

Hello and welcome to this, the second edition of Forbidden, everyone's
favourite AmigaGuide short story collection (probably because it's the
only one of its kind... though correct me if I'm wrong, /please/. :)

This time around the fiction isn't /all/ mine, in fact there's nearly
as much contributory work as there is from my own hand. Admittedly the
first release of Forbidden was crammed full of stories by myself and
noone else - but to be quite honest I wasn't sure if the idea would 
take off. Thankfully it seems to have proved quite popular, so here's
the deal: Forbidden is a platform for any writers who'd like to send
me their work and have it distributed in this form. I won't take shit,
so please don't send me anything pointlessly trivial, but I will accept
a wide range of genres and styles. I am especially interested in 
experimental works.

Send your stories (no word limits, but the shorter the better) to me
in ascii format - and that means no alien fileformats, please - at 
this address: 4 Alloe Field Place, Illingworth, Halifax, HX2 9ES. Or
if you've got email access: ajc@ajco.demon.co.uk.

All contributors do, of course, get full credit, plus a copy of each
new issue of Forbidden as and when they arrive. If in doubt, just get
in touch, your stories and letters will be treated in the strictest
confidence.

As usual please may I remind you that some of the stories contained
within this file contain strong language and scenes of a disturbing
nature, ie: I wouldn't recommend putting a printed copy of Forbidden 
under your baby daughter's pillow. I also have a big problem with 
accurate spelling and grammar - these rules are thrown out of the window
in the world of Forbidden, so if you spot a mistake, don't get orgasmic,
the chances are I've seen it but don't give a toss. :)

Feedback from the fiction is most welcome. All comments will be passed
on to the relevant author. Until next time - enjoy.




Andy


