dread of what she was about to see.  As if possessed of its own free 
will, her hand reached up towards the edge of the curtain.  She 
grasped it firmly, and stopped.  She knew what she would see, maybe 
if this time she didn't look then she could convince herself that he 
wasn't there.  Her hand pulled aside the curtain.  He was there.  His 
shadow crossed the boundaries of the tree below the window.  The rain 
obscured the view but she could tell he would be looking up at her.
