sight and drew the curtains.  If she had wanted to cast the image 
from her mind, she had failed.  She could see the scene below as if 
it had been physically burned onto her mind. 
 She could see the rain whipped tree, shaking in the uneven wind.  
She could almost feel the intrusion of the shadow that lurked beneath 
the weaving fringes of the tree's edge.
  
