remembered the fun they had.  Remembered her increased awareness of 
the figure that she tended to see when she looked around whilst out 
walking. When she asked him about it.  Of course he always denied it. 
  Abbey reached into the drawer set under the desk.  Her hand groped 
blindly, until she found the edges of the box.  She pulled it up on 
to the desk.  Her hands encircled the edge of the lid.  Pausing, 
whilst the memories flew thick and fast, she took off the lid. 
  Inside had the musty smell of things not used often. There were 
wads of papers, all starting to brown at the corners.  She lifted the 
top on out.  It was the first letter.

"Here, Anna, look at this."  "It came this morning, what do you 
think?"  "Yes I thought it was a bit creepy too."  "Youre right it 
probably is a trick.  In fact I think it might have been Dave, you 
know how he is."  Still slightly worried.  "Oh, hes in America.  Oh.  
Well it must have been somebody like that."  Looking at the letter. 
"I'll be there.  Always."

"I'll be there.  Always."  
  It was true the sentence on the sheet in front of her.  He will be. 
