Abbey got up from her chair and put her slippers on.  She didnt need 
shoes, she didnt go outside any more.  He was there.  Always.  Her 
door was open and she walked down the corridor.  She noticed the 
picture out of the corner of her eye.  The new warden was coming soon 
and there were pictures of him, with the other staff on the staff 
photo board.  The picture looked at her.  "Well be together, Abbey, 
always." Her eyes fixed on the board, she started screaming.  She 
collapsed slowly, but didnt stop screaming.

He wasn't always around, but he was today.  She was walking in the 
garden and saw him.  Usually he would only be there every other day.  
He had killed her friends and she had been waiting for this moment.  
  He was facing the other way seated on a bench.  She slowly walked 
up behind him.  Her shoes making no sound,  the weight of the stolen 
knife heavy in her hands.  She stood behind him.  Alerted by some 
strange and unexplainable sense, he turned round.  She slashed at the 
throat and cut true.  Blood started pouring down his front.  "Abbey?" 
He looked suprised. She had stabbed him lots.  His face continued to 
stare in the old familiar way, full of friendship and adoration.  She 
couldnt stand it, she cut his face. She cut his face so much you 
